Shipments to Alaska and Hawaii are higher because air shipment is required. Most firearms are shipped within 5 days of receipt of payment. We prefer shipping at the beginning of the week to avoid firearms in transit over weekends. 

We package all shipments carefully and insure them for the full purchase price, rounded up to the next $100. In the unlikely event that damage occurs, it is important that you save all packaging material for the claims process. Optics are shipped Priority Mail and most other non-firearm shipments are shipped First Class. 

Returns: Our return policy is simple. If for any reason you are not pleased with your purchase, you may return your item for a refund. The only exception is ammunition, it cannot be returned. It is important to us that you are happy. Guns cannot be fired or dissembled before returning them and must be returned in the same condition as received. Notification of a return must occur with-in 3 days of receipt at your dealer

postcontent:
Newport side by side 12 Ga. shotgun.

Very old turn of the century weapon.

Shotguns of that era used a 2 9/16ths " shot shell.
So a qualified gunsmith should be consulted to determine if modern ammunition can be used.

What I was able to research was that all NEWPORT shotguns were made by either Crescent Fire Arm Company, Iver Johnson's Arms & Cycle Works, W. H. Davenport Arms Company or Stevens Arms & Tool Co. Again according to my research. the Model CN and Model WN were made by both Crescent and Iver Johnson.

I f found that Aguila makes a #7 1/2 shot 1.75" 'mini' shell that will work for this gun.
http://www.midwayusa.com/Product/255579 ... -box-of-20

Shotgun is in good shape, no rust and appropriate patina for age.
Wood retains most of finish.
Matching serials on forearm & metal catch for forearm
Forearm a touch " wobbly "

title: For Sale:  Daewoo DP-51 / Lionheart
postcontent:
This is a nice DP-51 which is the military version of the new Lionheart pistol. It is based on the S&W 59 series with the addition of the "triple action" trigger system.

Daewoo K5 / DP51 / Lionheart pistol is short recoil operated, locked breech weapon. It uses a conventional Browning-type locking system, with two lugs on the barrel engaging cuts inside the slide. Locking and unlocking is controlled by the cam-shaped lug at the bottom of the barrel. Frame of the pistol is made from aluminium alloy; all other parts are made from steel. Trigger is of “triple action” type. This means that other than traditional double or single action fire modes it has “fast action” mode, apparently borrowed from FN’s GP “Fast Action” pistol. In this mode hammer is cocked by the cycle of the slide, then it is pushed forward by the pressure on the hammer head. In this position, the main spring remains cocked, so only light pressure on the trigger is necessary to recock the hammer and fire the gun in the “double action manner”. Or, alternatively, hammer can be recocked manually to be fired in single action for maximum first-shot accuracy. Sights are fixed, with the rear sight dovetailed to the slide. Ambidextrous levers at both sides of the frame, above and behind grip panels. To set on safe: pull the lever up. To disengage safety: pull the lever down; red dot will appear on the frame.

Mine includes 1 10rd Magazine, a nylon holster, and 20 rounds of Hornady XTP 124gr hollow points (which work very well in this gun)

My only trade interests are for a Sig P6/P225 or Sig P228

title: For Trade:  Beautiful Bulgarian AK-74 - Blued Steel Finish and Wood Furniture
postcontent:
Up for trade/sale is a very nice AK-74 built on a numbers matching Bulgarian parts kit. This gun has been finished with a unique deep blue finish on all metal parts, which is seamlessly complemented by the classic lines and intricate grain of the gloss finished wood furniture. This combination offers the reliability of a Kalashnikov rifle, but with a classy wood and steel finish that is more typical of American or Western European produced rifles. 

The barrel is chrome-lined and has only 70 rounds down the pipe to test for function. The gun functions reliability as expected from an AK, and the 5.45x39 round produces negligible recoil. 

The pistol grip is custom made from hickory wood and is very comfortable. The finger grooves and thumb and trigger finger rests make the gun fit your hand like a glove.

This AK-74 has been built using 6 US-made parts, so reliable surplus magazines can be used. This gun comes with one red Bulgarian Circle 21 30 round magazine and one black Tapco 30 round magazine.

The trigger is a Tapco G-2 that is relatively light and smooth. An axis pin retaining plate has been used for quick fire control group disassembly and reassembly.  

I also have a fairly large supply of 7N6 5.45x39 surplus ammo available if interested. Please email me with any questions or to request more pictures or details. I will be happy to answer any inquiries. I would be willing to ship through FFLs and would also do face-to-face private party transfer. Thanks for looking!

title: For Sale:  CZ50 .32ACP Semi-Auto Pistol w/Ammo & Accessories
postcontent:
Here's a numbers matching CZ50 .32 ACP double action semi-auto pistol. 

The CZ50 succeeded the CZ24, 27 & 38, and was a staple with Czech police units for many years. It was later improved and served on for years more as the CZ70. 

The CZ50 is a well built all steel pistol that is quite similar to the Walther PPK. As with all CZ built firearms quality is high and function/reliability is excellent.

This particular pistol is in very good condition. It retains about 85% of it's original finish. However there are some rubs/thin spots in the bluing resulting from years of being carried in a holster. Absolutely no rust or pitting though and the bore is bright and shiny.

Grips are very good with no cracks or dings, and function is 100%. 

Pistol comes in it's original importer box with two genuine original CZ thumb rest magazines.  

Additionally a CZ cleaning rod and an original CZ holster made specifically for the CZ50 or the CZ70 is included. This holster has become quite hard to find. 

Finally there are two 50 round boxes of Fiocchi .32ACP ammo included. Ammo is recent production brass case with 73 grain FMJ bullets. 

Asking price is $350. Local FTF sale only to a Florida resident of proper age who can legally own a firearm in Florida. 

Thanks for looking.

title: For Sale:  M249 Machine Gun barrel.
postcontent: Noveske chrome lined barrels are cold hammer forged and made with the material callouts and manufacturing process for the M249 Machine Gun barrel. The cold hammer forging process work hardens the steel around a rifled mandrel, which creates the lands and grooves. These barrels are chambered in 5.56mm NATO. The barrel is then chrome lined to the spec for a M249 Machine Gun barrel, which is about twice as thick as that of an M4 barrel. The end result is a rifle that can be run hard day after day. Having been part of many excellent training opportunities, I have seen how a barrel may experience serious trauma from high rates of fire and sustained high temperatures. For any high round count, high temp, heavy shooting, Noveske recommends their chrome lined barrel.
